      <description>&lt;p&gt;Source: &lt;a href=&#34;https://divyaprabandham.koyil.org/index.php/2018/03/siriya-thirumadal/&#34;&gt;TW&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;SrI: SrImathE SatakOpAya nama: SrImathE rAmAnujAya nama: SrImath varavaramunayE nama:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://divyaprabandham.koyil.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/vayalali-manavalan-e1522394213281.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;figure class=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;https://divyaprabandham.koyil.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/vayalali-manavalan-e1522394213281.jpg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img src=&#34;https://divyaprabandham.koyil.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/vayalali-manavalan-e1522394213281.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; title=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://acharyas.koyil.org/index.php/sriman-narayanan/&#34;&gt;vayalAli maNavALan&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=&#34;http://acharyas.koyil.org/index.php/sri-mahalakshmi/&#34;&gt;thAyAr&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://divyaprabandham.koyil.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/kaliyan_uthsavam_thiruvali_thirunagari_thirumangai_azhvar-Large.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;figure class=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;a href=&#34;https://divyaprabandham.koyil.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/kaliyan_uthsavam_thiruvali_thirunagari_thirumangai_azhvar-Large.jpg&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;img src=&#34;https://divyaprabandham.koyil.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/kaliyan_uthsavam_thiruvali_thirunagari_thirumangai_azhvar-Large.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; title=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://acharyas.koyil.org/index.php/thirumangai-azhwar/&#34;&gt;thirumangai AzhwAr&lt;/a&gt; with kumudhavalli nAchchiyAr&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;thirumangai AzhwAr has composed a beautiful prabandham named siRiya thirumadal. In this prabandham, he is feeling the separation from emperumAn and due to the great sorrow in separation, he assumes a feminine mood (as parakAla nAyaki) and performs madal [madal is an activity where the man/woman would hurl accusations on his/her beloved in the hopes to convince the other person for marriage].&lt;/p&gt;</description>
